                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/3943a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-27T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 27, 1919—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7549. Department desires to call your attention to the fact that the Embassy is
                    not keeping it advised of the general attitude of the French Press, and more
                    especially the reported changes in sentiment towards the American program in the
                    League of Nations. The American correspondents in Paris are sending daily
                    reports on this subject, and it is therefore embarrassing that the Embassy has
                    failed to keep the Department advised. Call your attention in particular that no
                    report was made as to attacks on our program which led to threat of moving Peace
                    Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
